          "raw_input": "eyJ0eXAiOiJkcG9wK2p3dCIsImFsZyI6IkVTMjU2IiwiandrIjp7Imt0eSI6IkVDIiwieCI6Imw4QkZkYW1Rcm02VW11RVBZNnIxcXlKRGxiM1V0M2pYV2l1S240LUdSM0EiLCJ5IjoiX2VLUHNJX3VzZV8yZmt6akRqaHFxOHFWZV8yb1Z2SW81akxRM01oNDF1TSIsImNydiI6IlAtMjU2In19.eyJqdGkiOiJBaHROaXhsRThPZyIsImh0bSI6IlBPU1QiLCJodHUiOiJodHRwczovL2FwaS5leGFtcGxlLmNvbS9wcm90ZWN0ZWQiLCJpYXQiOjE1NjIyNjI2MTgsImF0aCI6InBfWkhocUlWVkZDN1lkYkdTQnFaLVRTY0E2WThsWENNSWJJdXR0TjI2dzAifQ",
          "signing_key_hint": "Client's ES256 Private Key",
          "final_output": "aBcDe...",
          "steps": [
            {
              "label": "1. Build JWT Header (includes Public Key)",
              "value": "{\n  \"typ\": \"dpop+jwt\",\n  \"alg\": \"ES256\",\n  \"jwk\": {\n    \"kty\": \"EC\",\n    \"x\": \"l8BFdamQrm6UmuEPY6r1qyJDlb3Ut3jXWiuKn4-GR3A\",\n    \"y\": \"_eKPsI_use_2fkzjDjhqq8qVe_2oVvIo5jLQ3Mh41uM\",\n    \"crv\": \"P-256\"\n  }\n}\n\nRFC 9449 \u00a74.2: jwk MUST be present in every DPoP proof header,\nincluding proofs sent to the resource server.\n\nThe RS uses the jwk to:\n  1. Verify the DPoP proof signature\n  2. Compute SHA-256(canonicalized jwk) \u2192 compare to cnf.jkt\n     in the access token to confirm key binding"
