            {
              "label": "2. Build JWT Payload (with ath)",
              "value": "{\n  \"jti\": \"AhtNixlE8Og\",\n  \"htm\": \"POST\",\n  \"htu\": \"https://api.example.com/protected\",\n  \"iat\": 1562262618,\n  \"ath\": \"p_ZHhqIVVFC7YdbGSBqZ-TScA6Y8lXCMIbIuttN26w0\"\n}\n\nath = BASE64URL(SHA-256(ASCII(access_token)))\n    = p_ZHhqIVVFC7YdbGSBqZ-TScA6Y8lXCMIbIuttN26w0\n\nRFC 9449 \u00a74.3: ath MUST be present when a DPoP proof\nis sent to a resource server. It binds this proof to\nexactly this access token \u2014 a stolen proof cannot be\nreplayed with a different token.\n\nNote: ath was NOT included in step 1 (token endpoint)\nbecause there was no access token yet at that point."
            },
            {
              "label": "3. Sign JWT",
              "value": "ES256(Base64Url(Header) + \".\" + Base64Url(Payload), PrivateKey) \u2192 Signature"
            }
          ]
        }
