      "explanation": "The client accesses the resource server with a fresh DPoP proof for this specific request. The proof includes the full public key (jwk) in the header and an access token hash (ath) in the payload \u2014 both required by RFC 9449 at the RS. The resource server verifies the signature using the embedded jwk, checks the key thumbprint matches cnf.jkt in the access token, and confirms the ath matches the presented token.",
      "annotations": [
        "RFC 9449 \u00a74.2: The jwk header MUST be present in every DPoP proof, including those sent to the resource server. The RS uses it to verify the proof signature and confirm the key matches cnf.jkt in the access token.",
        "RFC 9449 \u00a74.3: ath (access token hash = BASE64URL(SHA-256(access_token))) MUST be included when the proof is sent to a resource server, binding this proof to the specific access token.",
        "The new DPoP proof is bound to the specific HTTP method and URL (htm, htu), preventing it from being intercepted and replayed on other endpoints.",
        "The RS validation chain: verify proof signature with jwk \u2192 compute SHA-256(jwk) \u2192 compare to cnf.jkt \u2192 verify ath matches presented access token."
      ]
    }
